# PATH

Path in linux based system is a way to set enviromental variables. 

PATH is constructed first from `/etc/paths`, then from the files in `/etc/paths.d`, and then from `.bash_profile`. 


### 'etc/path`

- Run following command and add your path
> sudo nano /etc/path

- Save and close terminal to reconstruct your PATH.

- Open terminal and run command
> echo $PATH

this should gives

```
/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/local/share/npm/bin

```




